Reasoning: The paper discusses metrics for usage of the SAO/NASA Astrophysics Data System (ADS), which is a digital library for astronomical literature. Therefore, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses how different types of users access the system, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a likely category. The paper also mentions how use of the ADS has evolved over the years in various regions of the world, which suggests cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the qualitative and quantitative changes in the use of the ADS, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as a possible category.
